The paper also involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) to generate images, which is a popular technique in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). 

The paper also involves the use of natural language processing techniques to parse the textual content, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of a conditional discriminator to model the correlations between words and image sub-regions, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). 

Finally, the paper involves experiments on the COCO dataset, which is a commonly used dataset in the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM).
